WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.660
Run for Your Life by Stephen Waller, Penguin Reader's Level

00:06.660 --> 00:10.380
1. The big street, with its

00:10.380 --> 00:15.680
cafes and shops and people, was behind them now. They

00:15.680 --> 00:20.580
walked slowly. It was quiet. Away

00:20.580 --> 00:26.820
from the cars and the noise, Kim was excited. She

00:26.820 --> 00:31.520
held onto Dave's hand. They were in a

00:31.520 --> 00:37.800
narrow street of tall houses and small shops. They heard

00:37.800 --> 00:40.060
a radio through an open window,

00:40.060 --> 00:47.840
a woman singing. Kim stopped and listened, but she did

00:47.840 --> 00:51.420
not understand the words. Her

00:51.420 --> 00:57.940
Spanish was good, but not very good. It was the

00:57.940 --> 01:00.560
fourth day of their stay in Barcelona.

01:03.080 --> 01:08.580
Kim and Dave were 17. They had the same Spanish

01:08.580 --> 01:13.140
teacher at school in Liverpool, a big town in

01:13.140 --> 01:20.060
England. Do you want to talk Spanish? Their teacher said,

01:20.820 --> 01:27.030
well, go to Spain. There were eight of

01:27.030 --> 01:31.870
them from the same school on this holiday. They went

01:31.870 --> 01:34.910
to school every morning and talked

01:34.910 --> 01:41.450
Spanish. Then, in the afternoons, they usually went out by

01:41.450 --> 01:44.690
bus and saw something in Barcelona.

01:45.690 --> 01:56.210
Important buildings, famous pictures, old photographs, something new every day.

01:57.730 --> 01:58.890
Today,

01:59.470 --> 02:04.990
Kim and Dave were not with their school friends. Dave

02:04.990 --> 02:10.790
did not want to go by bus. He wanted to

02:10.790 --> 02:17.870
look around the old town, not the famous buildings, not

02:17.870 --> 02:21.030
the big shopping streets with the banks

02:21.030 --> 02:28.090
and cafes and book shops. He was interested in the

02:28.090 --> 02:31.090
little streets behind the old market.

02:32.310 --> 02:39.730
The dangerous old town, people said. But Dave was not

02:39.730 --> 02:44.590
frightened. There are dangerous streets in

02:44.590 --> 02:51.730
Liverpool too, he said. You can't see a town or

02:51.730 --> 02:57.110
its people only from a bus. It will be exciting.

02:59.630 --> 03:03.690
They did not try to remember the names of the

03:03.690 --> 03:09.770
streets. They did not have a street plan. At every

03:09.770 --> 03:15.470
corner, they stopped and looked. Then they came to an

03:15.470 --> 03:19.770
interesting little street. It was very narrow,

03:20.690 --> 03:29.010
very old, they thought. Dave took a photograph. Kim looked

03:29.010 --> 03:35.230
up. The houses were very tall. The windows

03:35.230 --> 03:39.610
up there were in the sun. But down in the

03:39.610 --> 03:45.590
street, it was dark. They came to a little open

03:45.590 --> 03:46.770
place with

03:46.770 --> 03:51.650
two or three trees and sat down. It was quiet.

03:53.310 --> 03:57.270
Suddenly there was a noise in one of the houses.

03:58.470 --> 04:02.930
A door opened and a man in a black shirt

04:02.930 --> 04:08.690
and jeans ran out. He stood at the open door

04:08.690 --> 04:09.870
and looked

04:09.870 --> 04:14.610
back into the house. Then he ran across the street.

04:16.290 --> 04:22.750
Is he coming over here? Kim asked. There was something

04:22.750 --> 04:26.630
frightening about the man. Dave did

04:26.630 --> 04:31.230
not answer. The man ran to the corner and looked

04:31.230 --> 04:37.710
around. Then he ran away. He put something in

04:37.710 --> 04:44.670
that rubbish bin. There were shouts from the house. A

04:44.670 --> 04:49.690
second man ran out into the street. He had

04:49.690 --> 04:54.850
long hair and dark glasses. He stood in the road

04:54.850 --> 04:59.870
and looked round. Perhaps he is looking for that

04:59.870 --> 05:06.610
man in the black shirt, said Dave. And look! He

05:06.610 --> 05:14.270
has got a gun! Kim looked. Dave was right. The

05:14.270 --> 05:18.710
long-haired man ran across the street and went round

05:18.710 --> 05:19.230
the corner.

05:21.110 --> 05:27.750
Let's get away from here. Kim said. I don't like

05:27.750 --> 05:34.710
this. But Dave was excited. Let's go and have a

05:34.710 --> 05:40.610
look in that rubbish bin. He said. There was a

05:40.610 --> 05:45.750
brown box in the bin. Dave took it out and

05:45.750 --> 05:46.290
opened

05:46.290 --> 05:50.790
it. A small white bag fell out.

05:52.270 --> 05:58.090
Drugs! He said. We'll take this to the police.

05:59.450 --> 06:05.990
Can I see? Kim took the little white bag and

06:05.990 --> 06:11.050
held it in her hand. She was suddenly very frightened.

06:11.850 --> 06:17.570
She looked round. Behind them there was a man there

06:17.570 --> 06:23.130
under the trees, watching them. The man

06:23.130 --> 06:29.330
moved. Kim looked at the bag in her hand. Suddenly

06:29.330 --> 06:36.510
she knew. Dave, that man, he's back. He's here.

06:37.150 --> 06:44.570
She said. The man was very near them now. He

06:44.570 --> 06:49.830
was not very tall with a thin white face and

06:49.830 --> 06:50.290
dark

06:50.290 --> 06:57.390
dangerous eyes. Give it to me. He said in Spanish.

06:58.930 --> 07:02.510
His frightening eyes moved quickly from Kim to

07:02.510 --> 07:08.830
Dave and back to Kim. You've got it. I saw

07:08.830 --> 07:23.210
you. Now give it back. Kim opened her mouth but

07:23.210 --> 07:32.490
the

07:32.490 --> 07:35.090
man then she saw the knife in the man's hand.

07:36.450 --> 07:41.130
She started to run. She ran into a small street

07:41.130 --> 07:46.750
on the left. She ran down two or three narrow

07:46.750 --> 08:02.470
streets but she did not see any people. She

08:03.110 --> 08:09.870
thought, I can't stop. But all the streets were the

08:09.870 --> 08:16.330
same. Where was she now? Suddenly she came

08:16.330 --> 08:22.350
round a corner and her legs went cold. The street

08:22.350 --> 08:27.690
did not go through. It stopped. There were some

08:27.690 --> 08:32.710
cars and a big old building, an old cinema perhaps,

08:33.590 --> 08:38.530
but there was no road through. Kim

08:38.530 --> 08:43.330
looked back. The man stood at the corner and waited.

08:44.550 --> 08:47.330
He started to walk slowly down the street.

08:48.410 --> 08:52.930
Kim looked round. There was a door in the building.

08:54.110 --> 08:59.370
She ran to it. It opened. She went in and

08:59.370 --> 08:59.730
shut

08:59.730 --> 09:04.470
the door behind her. He won't come after me in

09:04.470 --> 09:13.350
here. Noise. People. Women. Talking. Shouting.

09:13.350 --> 09:20.370
Moving their arms. The market. She was in the market

09:20.370 --> 09:25.210
in the old town near the big shopping street.

09:26.350 --> 09:31.150
That door was a back door to the market and

09:31.150 --> 09:37.450
the big street was very near. She started to walk

09:37.450 --> 09:42.650
through the market. She was in a slow moving river

09:42.650 --> 09:47.310
of people with heavy shopping bags. She

09:47.310 --> 09:52.930
moved with the river. Every time one person stopped and

09:52.930 --> 10:07.430
looked at some fruit or fish, all of them

10:07.430 --> 10:12.910
stood for the family. Then in the sea of faces,

10:13.730 --> 10:19.490
Kim saw those same dark eyes again, watching

10:19.490 --> 10:26.450
her. He was here in the market. Kim started to

10:26.450 --> 10:29.990
run. There were shopping bags under her feet.

10:30.790 --> 10:36.890
She fell and got up again. People shouted at her.

10:38.070 --> 10:41.990
One woman tried to catch hold of her, but Kim

10:41.990 --> 10:48.670
did not stop. Then she looked back. The man was

10:48.670 --> 10:54.810
not behind her now. Perhaps she was wrong. Those

10:54.810 --> 11:00.730
eyes. Perhaps it was not the same man. She saw

11:00.730 --> 11:05.470
the big street now. She saw the sun and the

11:05.470 --> 11:05.850
trees.

11:07.350 --> 11:12.110
Suddenly a hand came down on her arm and held

11:12.110 --> 11:12.870
onto her.

11:13.890 --> 11:20.590
Are you Kim Steel? The woman asked. She was tall,

11:21.370 --> 11:24.770
about thirty. She had a friendly look.

11:27.950 --> 11:35.570
Kim did not understand. Yes, she started to say. But

11:35.570 --> 11:39.930
how do you? Then in the woman's hand,

11:39.930 --> 11:46.170
she saw a photo and in Spanish, the word police.

11:48.030 --> 11:52.950
I am Inspector Lothano, but please call me Anna.

11:54.570 --> 12:01.690
The police woman smiled. Your friend Dave found us. He

12:01.690 --> 12:04.630
is in the car. Come with me.

12:06.230 --> 12:10.750
Kim sat in the car with Dave. There was a

12:10.750 --> 12:15.970
man with Anna. He had long hair and dark glasses.

12:17.690 --> 12:25.770
Now Kim understood. He was a policeman too. She gave

12:25.770 --> 12:34.610
Anna the little white bag and asked about

12:34.610 --> 12:41.290
that. That's it. That's right, Anna said. She looked at

12:41.290 --> 12:42.530
the long-haired man.

12:43.710 --> 12:49.170
Nacho here nearly caught him in his house. You saw

12:49.170 --> 12:54.350
that. Vidal, that's his name, was lucky.

12:55.280 --> 13:01.370
He got away. But we want him. And you can

13:01.370 --> 13:05.650
do something for us. Nacho smiled.

13:07.510 --> 13:17.210
Yes, Kim said slowly. But Vidal knows you now, Kim.

13:18.110 --> 13:21.830
And he wants his drugs. Listen.

13:22.830 --> 13:28.030
This is my plan. You go back to that place

13:28.030 --> 13:34.190
near Vidal's house. Vidal will be there and he'll see

13:34.190 --> 13:34.550
you.

13:35.710 --> 13:42.370
We'll be there too. But Vidal won't see us. He'll

13:42.370 --> 13:45.070
think she's looking for her friend.

13:45.070 --> 13:53.730
I can't do it. Don't be frightened. Vidal won't get

13:53.730 --> 13:58.770
near you. We'll stop him. But he'll try.

13:59.890 --> 14:02.630
And then we'll catch him.

14:05.830 --> 14:09.570
What do you think, Dave? Say something.

14:11.370 --> 14:17.990
Well, uh, Anna and Nacho will be near. And they

14:17.990 --> 14:20.230
know all about these things.

14:21.530 --> 14:27.230
But this Vidal man has got a knife. Perhaps he'll

14:27.230 --> 14:28.110
kill me?

14:29.630 --> 14:34.450
Well, yes. But I'll be there too, you know.

14:35.670 --> 14:37.190
You do it then.

14:38.230 --> 14:42.490
Ah, but Vidal doesn't know me.

14:44.150 --> 14:49.790
Kim said yes and Nacho talked on the car radio.

14:51.010 --> 14:54.170
Then they drove round behind the market.

14:55.110 --> 14:58.950
Kim got out and shut the car door.

15:00.010 --> 15:04.490
She walked to the corner. Then she looked back.

15:06.030 --> 15:11.570
Anna smiled at her. Dave's face was very white.

15:13.530 --> 15:18.070
Kim was frightened. These things were exciting in the cinema.

15:19.570 --> 15:20.910
But this was not a game.

15:22.230 --> 15:26.010
Anna and Nacho were there. She knew that.

15:27.050 --> 15:29.230
But this Vidal was clever.

15:30.350 --> 15:32.970
Perhaps he knew about their little plan.

15:34.490 --> 15:35.610
And he was dangerous.

15:37.990 --> 15:42.230
She was back in the same street now. There was

15:42.230 --> 15:42.670
the house.

15:43.710 --> 15:45.030
The door was shut.

15:46.490 --> 15:48.190
And there was the rubbish bin.

15:49.550 --> 15:52.890
Two or three people came down the street.

15:54.490 --> 15:56.690
Kim walked slowly across the road.

15:57.690 --> 16:01.870
She looked round. Then up at the windows of the

16:01.870 --> 16:02.210
houses.

16:03.170 --> 16:04.290
She waited.

16:06.090 --> 16:12.250
He's here. He's watching me. I can feel it.

16:14.020 --> 16:19.450
Then she saw him. The black shirt. The thin face.

16:20.290 --> 16:26.270
It was eyes. It was Vidal. He was very near

16:26.270 --> 16:26.670
her.

16:28.130 --> 16:29.990
Kim looked across the street.

16:30.990 --> 16:32.590
She was ready to run.

16:33.810 --> 16:35.370
Then she heard Vidal.

16:36.170 --> 16:41.990
He said something. The same thing again and again.

16:44.130 --> 16:45.730
What's he saying?

16:46.590 --> 16:50.310
Kim thought. Is he talking to me?

16:51.530 --> 16:57.110
She looked at him. He did not move. Only his

16:57.110 --> 16:57.970
mouth moved.

16:58.970 --> 17:02.750
This time she understood the words.

17:04.010 --> 17:07.990
Give it to me. Or you're dead.

17:09.250 --> 17:09.850
He said.

17:11.690 --> 17:15.870
A car drove around the corner very quickly and stopped.

17:17.070 --> 17:21.910
Anna and Nacho jumped out. They held guns.

17:23.030 --> 17:24.170
Anna shouted.

17:25.170 --> 17:30.210
Police. Don't move. We've got guns.

17:32.490 --> 17:36.590
Vidal suddenly jumped at Kim and caught her.

17:37.830 --> 17:42.690
Kim tried to hit him to get away. But he

17:42.690 --> 17:44.210
held onto her hair.

17:45.390 --> 17:50.690
He was thin but strong. Then she saw the knife.

17:52.170 --> 17:55.770
You'll be sorry, Vidal. Nacho shouted.

17:56.810 --> 18:00.110
You can't get out of here. Think, man.

18:01.610 --> 18:05.890
Throw the knife down and take your hands from the

18:05.890 --> 18:06.190
girl.

18:07.530 --> 18:13.410
But Vidal held onto Kim. He shouted to the police.

18:14.630 --> 18:19.250
Get back in the car. Or I'll do it.

18:20.690 --> 18:26.110
He held the knife near Kim's face. She shot her

18:26.110 --> 18:26.570
eyes.

18:27.510 --> 18:30.170
Time moved very slowly.

18:31.930 --> 18:34.950
She saw a face at the window of one of

18:34.950 --> 18:36.670
the houses across the road.

18:37.770 --> 18:43.250
Anna and Nacho moved back to the car. Their guns

18:43.250 --> 18:44.050
were ready.

18:45.170 --> 18:46.930
But Vidal stood behind Kim.

18:48.290 --> 18:55.890
You're coming with me. Suddenly there were excited shouts from

18:55.890 --> 18:57.510
behind the police car.

18:58.610 --> 19:02.810
It was Dave. He ran across the street.

19:04.210 --> 19:05.910
What's he doing?

19:06.850 --> 19:10.830
Kim thought. Does he want to see me dead?

19:14.690 --> 19:22.070
Anna tried to stop him. Come back. This man is

19:22.070 --> 19:22.750
dangerous.

19:24.030 --> 19:28.790
She shouted. Dave ran to the rubbish bin.

19:29.670 --> 19:34.470
He stopped, took the bin in his hands and held

19:34.470 --> 19:36.470
it up over his head.

19:37.110 --> 19:38.930
Then he threw it.

19:40.830 --> 19:46.150
The rubbish bin went over Kim's head and hit Vidal.

19:47.550 --> 19:52.030
Rubbish fell round his feet. He fell.

19:53.370 --> 19:57.710
Kim quickly took the knife from his hand and threw

19:57.710 --> 19:58.290
it away.

19:59.350 --> 20:05.810
There were excited shouts. Kim looked up. It was Anna

20:05.810 --> 20:06.850
and Nacho.

20:08.150 --> 20:12.030
He's all yours now. Said Dave.

20:13.490 --> 20:18.610
Nacho held Vidal's hands behind his back and took him

20:18.610 --> 20:18.950
away.

20:20.350 --> 20:22.650
Kim fell into Anna's arms.

20:24.410 --> 20:28.850
Later they drove back to the hotel in a police

20:28.850 --> 20:29.330
car.

20:30.390 --> 20:32.130
Kim looked at Dave.

20:33.570 --> 20:39.110
Don't say it. I know. It was dangerous.

20:40.310 --> 20:45.250
But I saw the bin and I thought, well, you

20:45.250 --> 20:48.130
know, I wanted to do something.

20:49.170 --> 20:54.290
I see these things in the cinema. There's always a

20:54.290 --> 20:55.250
strong man.

20:56.470 --> 20:59.650
Today I was the strong man.

21:01.270 --> 21:05.750
Yes. And I was nearly the dead girlfriend.

21:07.270 --> 21:10.830
You see a lot of them in the cinema too?

21:12.770 --> 21:17.770
Let's not think about it, Dave. It's not important now.

21:19.450 --> 21:24.290
The important thing now is, what are we doing tomorrow?

21:25.550 --> 21:29.050
We didn't see all of the old town today.

21:30.170 --> 21:32.480
Let's go out again tomorrow afternoon.

21:34.190 --> 21:35.430
Have a walk round.

21:36.610 --> 21:40.530
You can't see a town only from a bus, you

21:40.530 --> 21:40.730
know.

21:42.710 --> 21:46.770
I'll go for a walk with you tomorrow to the

21:46.770 --> 21:47.770
bus stop.

